The Canadian government's budget deficitrose to 1.78 billion dlrs in January from 1.67 billion dlrs inthe same month last year, the finance department said.    But the deficit in the first 10 months of the fiscal yearwhich began on April 1, 1986, fell to 22.36 billion dlrs from25.74 billion dlrs in the same period a year ago.    January revenues rose to 7.96 billion dlrs from 7.56billion dlrs while expenditures grew to 9.74 billion dlrs from9.23 billion dlrs. Revenues in the first 10 months increased to70.06 billion dlrs from 62.30 billion while expenditures grewto 92.42 billion dlrs from 88.05 billion.            Reuter&#3;